CSRLIN
==========

Returns the row position of the cursor

Syntax:
declare function Csrlin ( ) as integer

Usage:
result = Csrlin

Return Value:
An `integer` specifying the current row of the cursor.

Description:
Returns the current row the cursor is on (i.e. the "cursor line"). The topmost
row is number `1`.

Examples:

Print "The cursor is on row:"; CsrLin

Differences from QB:
None

See also:
`Locate`
`Pos`
